  <heading>SUBPT</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Subtract checked pointer</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction subtracts an optionally-shifted register value
from a base address register value, and writes the result to the
destination register. The optionally-shifted register value is treated
as the offset.</para>
      <para>If the operation would have generated a result where the most significant 8 bits
of the result register differ from the most significant 8 bits of the base
register, then the result is modified such that it is likely to be non-canonical
when used as an address.</para>
    </authored>
  </desc>
